main event: Two unidentified objects were visually observed moving toward the western sky in Easthampton, New York on August 20, 1966.
interesting points: The objects faded from view after several minutes of observation.,This sighting was reported by the same observer for the fifth time since March.,The objects were described as possibly being aircraft.,The observation was made visually without any physical evidence collected.,The witness included a personal account of having similar experiences in the past.
witness description: A 37-year-old male who has previously reported multiple sightings.
